After racing for 12 long days through the desert and covering over 7,500km, Sam Sunderland secured his third career podium at the Dakar with an admirable top-three result.

Matthias Walkner finished inside the top 10 despite an early setback, and rally rookie Daniel Sanders impressed the entire paddock with his fourth place result.

Halfway through the race and Manuel Lettenbichler moves into the lead at Red Bull Romaniacs!

After fighting up front all day, with the retirement of his closest rival, Mani now enjoys a healthy 23-minute advantage at the top of the standings.

FMF KTM Factory Racing's Trystan Hart enjoyed his best result of the race so far with seventh.

Following a night camping under the stars, the KTM 300 EXC TPI riders have two more days left to race.

node.text:
Manuel Lettenbichler has finished as runner-up on Offroad Day 1 at Red Bull Romaniacs. 

Building his speed throughout the day, Mani got his head down when the going got tough to finish just three and a half minutes down on the leader after close to five hours of racing.

FMF KTM Factory Racing's Trystan Hart finished 11th on his first ever full day at Romaniacs.

With tomorrow marking the first half of the event's marathon stage, a gruelling two days of riding await all competitors at the world's toughest hard enduro rallye!

Photos: @future7media

After another closely fought day at the GP of Sweden, Josep Garcia topped the Enduro2 class with a masterful display of riding in the tough, hot conditions. 

With the top five in the EnduroGP class separated by just seconds after all nine tests, Garcia ultimately claimed fourth place to defend his second overall in the EnduroGP Championship standings.

Josep will now enjoy a well-earned summer break before racing resumes with the 2021 ISDE, held in Italy from August 30.

Once again locked in a three-way fight for the EnduroGP podium places, Josep Garcia finished day one at the GP of Sweden as runner-up.

Just over 10 seconds behind going into the 10th and final test of the day, Josep gave his all, but unfortunately a crash ended up costing the valuable seconds he needed and the young Spaniard had to settle for second. 

Racing concludes in Sweden tomorrow with day two of round four of the 2021 FIM Enduro World Championship.

@mxgp | Herlings out of Czech Grand Prix

The Red Bull KTM Factory Racing rider will not take part in the fifth round of MXGP this weekend at Loket, and will continue to evaluate the state of his left shoulder injury sustained last Sunday at the Dutch Grand Prix.

“I don’t have pain in my shoulder for day-to-day life but sports and especially something like motocross is a different story," Herlings says. "We’ll sit out Loket with the aim to come back 100%. It’s a shame and something that wasn’t my fault but it is what it is.”
